<img src="images/washington.gif" alt="WA" title="Meet in/around Vancouver" align="left">
</dt><dd><div style="">Old Apple Tree Park, 110 SE Columbia Way, Vancouver, WA 98661 <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=110+SE+Columbia+Way%2C+Vancouver%2C+WA+98661&amp;by=5:30+p.m.&amp;on=06/22/11" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="images/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a></div>
5:30pm, Roughly 2 hours<div style="">
<em>Ride across the Land Bridge and along Burnt Bridge Creek Trail with a
 local planner and landscape architect to learn more about the native 
plants that improve livability and add beauty for many species, 
including us. We'll begin at the Old Apple Tree and cycle to the Burnt 
Bridge Creek trailhead on Devine, then east along the creek to Andresen.
