on a full city lot; Emerson Street Garden, a site demonstrating a 
low-tech, sustainable method of lead removal; OUR Garden, a garden 
managed by the Urban Farm Collective as a vegetable garden; and Fargo 
Forest Garden, an urban food forest next to the Waypost Cafe. We'll 
finish up at the Waypost, and can stay there for food and drinks 
afterwards and be serenaded by Halley the Bicycling Harpist.</em>
<br>Ari Rosner, c<span>ommunity_engagement<img src="images/at.gif" alt=" at " border="0">albertagrocery.coop</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/calforum.php?id=2282" title="0 messages"><img src="images/forum.gif" alt="[forum]" border="0"></a>
</div></dd>
