6:00pm<div style="">
<em>Help the City conduct the annual Summer Bike Counts.
<br>
<br>Portland collects some of the best data on bicycle use in the 
country and it's all because of the tremendous support we get from 
volunteers. Volunteering fun! It requires only two hours of your time 
and the information you collectively provide us is invaluable.
<br>
<br>All new volunteers must attend a training. It involves pizza and 
soda, is informative and fun and is mandatory if you haven't counted 
before.</em>
<br>Nick Falbo, n<span>ick.falbo<img src="images/at.gif" alt=" at " border="0">portlandoregon.gov</span>, <a href="http://www.portlandonline.com/transportation/index.cfm?c=44671&amp;">Portland Bicycle Counts Information</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://shift2bikes.org/cal/calforum.php?id=2489" title="0 messages"><img src="images/forum.gif" alt="[forum]" border="0"></a>
</div></dd>
